comment: The cofinality of a limit aleph is the same as the cofinality of its argument, so if ` ( aleph `` A ) < A ` , then ` ( aleph `` A ) ` is singular. Conversely, if ` ( aleph `` A ) ` is regular (i.e. weakly inaccessible), then ` ( aleph `` A ) = A ` , so ` A ` has to be rather large (see ~ alephfp ). Proposition 11.13 of [TakeutiZaring] p. 103. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 9-Mar-2013.)
